Congressional leaders have reached a bipartisan funding framework that aims to prevent a government shutdown and protect national priorities. The framework reflects the funding levels negotiated and signed into law last spring. It rejects significant cuts to programs that support hardworking families and aims to pass full-year funding bills without extreme policies. The leadership of Senators Schumer and Jeffries in reaching this framework is appreciated. However, congressional Republicans are urged to fulfill their responsibility to fund important domestic and national security priorities and to stop threatening a government shutdown. The article concludes by calling on Republicans to take action.